This is half issue and half PR (PR because there's a possible fix but issue because I don't care how it's fixed).

Building with Intel compilers (icpc (ICC) 16.0.3 20160415) with CPP standard 11 or 14, I get a compile error for some of the tests. This also happens in my project when exporting a function whose arguments are void. In terms of something simple to understand, I've added `void kw_func5() { }` to test_kwargs_and_defaults and tested it against `None`. The build error I get is below.

```
[ 50%] Building CXX object tests/CMakeFiles/pybind11_tests.dir/test_kwargs_and_defaults.cpp.o
/theoryfs2/ds/cdsgroup/psi4-compile/externals/pybind11/include/pybind11/cast.h(1261): error: a constexpr function cannot have a parameter of nonliteral type "pybind11::handle"
      static constexpr bool load_impl_sequence(handle, index_sequence<>) { return true; }
                            ^
          detected during:
            instantiation of "bool pybind11::detail::argument_loader<Args...>::load_impl(pybind11::handle, pybind11::handle, ...) [with Args=<>]" at line 1231
            instantiation of "bool pybind11::detail::argument_loader<Args...>::load_args(pybind11::handle, pybind11::handle) [with Args=<>]" at line 124 of "/theoryfs2/ds/cdsgroup/psi4-compile/externals/pybind11/include/pybind11/pybind11.h"
            instantiation of "void pybind11::cpp_function::initialize(Func &&, Return (*)(Args...), const Extra &...) [with Func=void (*&)(), Return=void, Args=<>, Extra=<pybind11::name, pybind11::scope, pybind11::sibling>]" at line 49 of "/theoryfs2/ds/cdsgroup/psi4-compile/externals/pybind11/include/pybind11/pybind11.h"
            instantiation of "pybind11::cpp_function::cpp_function(Return (*)(Args...), const Extra &...) [with Return=void, Args=<>, Extra=<pybind11::name, pybind11::scope, pybind11::sibling>]" at line 563 of "/theoryfs2/ds/cdsgroup/psi4-compile/externals/pybind11/include/pybind11/pybind11.h"
            instantiation of "pybind11::module &pybind11::module::def(const char *, Func &&, const Extra &...) [with Func=void (*)(), Extra=<>]" at line 49 of "/theoryfs2/ds/cdsgroup/psi4-compile/externals/pybind11/tests/test_kwargs_and_defaults.cpp"

```

The key line is in `cast.h`: `static constexpr bool load_impl_sequence(handle, bool, index_sequence<>) { return true; }`. @bennybp and @ryanmrichard have knowledgeably fixed my problem in two ways, both shown below. I've included the second in this PR.

```
    // current state of code
    //static constexpr bool load_impl_sequence(handle, index_sequence<>) { return true; }
    // fixes my problem
    //static bool load_impl_sequence(handle, index_sequence<>) { return true; }
    // also fixes my problem. in this PR.
    static constexpr bool load_impl_sequence(const handle &, index_sequence<>) { return true; }
```

fixes #2259 

Since the capnp schema require the ability to load files with relative paths, the zip-import functionality won't work. The `setup()` function has a `zip_safe` option that let's us specify that the archive must be unpacked when installed.

@jcasner fyi
@rhyolight please review
